These are my opinions on Mages having root.<br>
<br>
If mages had root then they could getto crowd control in groups.<br>
This is one of the few utility functions a wizard bring to a group.<br>
<br>
Wizard - Magical damage (nukes), Evac, getto crowd control, TL people out when they leave the group.<br>
<br>
Mage - Magical damage (nukes), Melee damage (pet), Debuff (for landing slow and magical damage), Coth (to save the puller), Magic enchancers (summoned items, Rods), DS on the MT<br>
<br>
In the higher PoP planes ie PoV, Root+Snare doesnt save you against adds (assuming your brave enough to solo there) because of the wonderfull &quot;This mob is immune to changes in run speed&quot; message.<br>
Also an unsnared add often means rooting while tanking (or running and getting more adds). This doesnt work very well given how hard the mobs hit and because they can stun.<br>
Training to the zone in is not acceptable in PoP zones because of the proximity to the graveyards.<br>
<br>
I have been in many PoV groups. All of these have had a cleric and an enchanter. One of the major issue in a PoV fight is getting the mobs slowed. My impression is that besides the mage pets and nukes they would choose a mage over a wizard because of the mages debuff line of spells.<br>
Also once a mage has landed the debuff , which they have do for the slow, their nukes are effectively at -70 (for Malosinia) and -35 (for Mala ) to resists.<br>
The new wizard draughts are at -50...<br>
The -300 to resist Lures are really too inefficent to use in xp groups.<br>
<br>
About Evac, Yes Evac is nice... but with the PoP graveyards Evac becomes less important. Having to fight you way back to you corpses naked is a thing of the past.<br>
Usually when I do Evac, some know it all (melee class usually) will be anoyed because he/she felt that it was premature.<br>
<br>
[edit]<br>
Note - In groups aggro avoidance is not really an issue... Why? because if I am chaining nuke + concussion I just go oom and have to sit though mobs to med.<br>
[/edit]<br>
<br>
Moozoo Sorcerer Povar<br>
Blades of Law<br>
