<br>
One charge of root on a summoned item will not change anything really but might give you a chance to live.  It would really suck to get killed at 60 by a green-weenie that has sow just because you didn't have a pet up, or it died already.<br>
<br>
Or to follow the Mage theme, they can give us a summoned root-like spell that can't be cast while having a Pet up, (give the message: Can't have more than one pet at once).  This would eliminate the extra power root would give to chain casting pets.  But on raids where you can't have a pet, at least you can help crowd control.  <br>
<br>
Ever try running through Burning woods with J-boots and a Sarnak with SOW starts chasing you = dead mage, unless you gate like a coward.  You might pull off a 10 second casting time pet while a mob is beating on you... if you even live to see if the spell got interrupted.<br>
<br>
Try doing Trials and have your first Banish *resisted*... you then have to either kite, put pet on mob chasing you, die, or hope the Paladin roots him for you (yeah a tank with 5000+ buffed hps, 1300+ AC,  LoH, and lots of nifty spells, has to root a mob for a pure caster... makes no sense to me)  ... not even sure if mobs in trials can be rooted, but you get my point. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 846<br> <font color=#333333>(1/12/03 8:23:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=375.topic&index=172>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Alternative to root maybe</span><hr size=1> Trial mobs can be rooted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=znailvh>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#333333>(1/13/03 7:55:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=375.topic&index=173>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Alternative to root maybe</span><hr size=1> Personaly I think that magicians should have root at about the same time clerics and wizards got pets that tank like magician pets.<br>
<br>
Traveling in pre-pop outdoor zones arent made easy by root. Invisibility and Levitation is by far better tools. And I dont consider it a challenge to run through Burning Woods with a warrior without invis, sow or jboots. Its easy to spot mobs in outdoor zones and avoid aggro. How hard can it be for an invisible levitating magician?<br>
<br>
Oh, if magicians do get a summoned root item I dont think it should have shorter casting time then normal root. Think 3 seconds and it sounds about right. But the idea of having long cast and even longer recast for a summoned item is at least an idea that could work without changing too much. This is if SOE for some reason thinks that magicians should have root. If the item is not nodrop then it would add a usefull item to summon for others as well. Again, asuming thats something magicians needs right now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eandori>Eandori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 492<br> <font color=#333333>(1/14/03 12:51:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=375.topic&index=174>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Alternative to root maybe</span><hr size=1> Yes I have played other classes.  But I have played my mage for YEARS.  OF COURSE I realize that we don't have defense other then Gate+pet.  Been playing this toon non-stop since 1999.<br>
<br>
Having Jboots, was game changing for me when I got them.  Getting an item that cast blind was game changing.  The root earring was the same thing, game changing.  I would be an idiot or a liar to say it was not a huge power/ability increase.  I noticed being able to do many more things I could not do before.<br>
<br>
When I'm crawling around dungeons, I can pull safer by rooting one mob, and killing the others that come.<br>
<br>
When I'm soloing, or grouping I can &quot;ghetto mez&quot; adds.<br>
<br>
Chaining pets is trivial now.<br>
<br>
I can fear-kite easily now with Root+Blind+high aggro before sending in pet.<br>
<br>
I can keep mobs on a tank while fighting better.<br>
<br>
I can root the mob chasing my group member and save their skin while my pet catches up and gets himself up the hate list.<br>
<br>
<br>
Yes, other classes get root.  Yes mages have a need for it.  No I'm not going to pretend that it was not game changing and powerfull to get it, because it was.   <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
